# Trim the Docker build context to the files actually needed for the multi-stage
# image build. Keeping the context lean means faster `docker build` (less data
# sent to the daemon) and avoids invalidating the `dependency:go-offline` cache
# layer when a developer's local `target/` is touched.
#
# IMPORTANT: do NOT add the following to this file -- the Dockerfile depends on them:
#   - mvnw
#   - .mvn/
#   - pom.xml
#   - src/

# --- Build outputs ---
target/
*.jar
*.war
*.class

# --- Version control ---
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# --- IDEs ---
.idea/
*.iml
*.ipr
*.iws
.vscode/
.settings/
.classpath
.project
.factorypath

# --- macOS ---
.DS_Store

# --- Logs and runtime artifacts ---
*.log
logs/
*.pid
hs_err_pid*

# --- Local study / refactor notes (gitignored too) ---
REFACTORING_NOTES.md

# --- Project docs not needed inside the build ---
HELP.md
CHANGELOG.md
README.md
docker/

# --- Test reports (we run with -DskipTests in the image build) ---
src/test/
